<HL>
   Pan American August Traffic
</HL>
<DATE>
09/13/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C5
</SO>
<CO>
   PN
</CO>
<IN>
AIRLINES (AIR)
</IN>
<LP>
   NEW YORK -- Pan Am Corp. said August traffic at its Pan
American World Airways unit rose 7.5% to 3.38 billion revenue
passenger miles, which it said was a single-month record for
the carrier, from 3.15 billion a year earlier.
   A revenue passenger mile is one paying passenger flown one
mile. The airline said its August load factor, or percentage
of available seats occupied, jumped to 77.8% from 76%.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   For the first eight months, Pan Am's traffic rose 10% to
21.4 billion revenue passenger miles from 19.46 billion. The
load factor rose to 68.7% from 66.7%.
