<HL>
   Business Brief -- Santa Fe Pacific Corp.:
   Debentures Are Accepted
   In a Debt-for-Equity Swap
</HL>
<DATE>
09/13/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C8
</SO>
<CO>
   SFX
</CO>
<IN>
BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)
RAILROADS (RAI)
BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)
</IN>
<LP>
   Santa Fe Pacific Corp., Chicago, said it has accepted for
exchange $215.6 million principal amount of its 16% senior
subordinated debentures, due 2003, under its previously
announced debt-for-equity swap.
   The railroad, real estate and natural resources concern
said debenture holders will receive 67.25 shares of its stock
plus $26.67 for each $1,000 principal amount of debentures
accepted for exchange. Santa Fe said it will issue 14.5
million common shares in the exchange offer.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Santa Fe said the debentures are being purchased on a pro
rata basis; the definitive pro rata factor is expected to be
announced on or about next Tuesday.
   The company said it is continuing with its plan to
refinance and redeem the remaining $565 million of debentures
outstanding on about Oct. 31 through the issuance of
long-term debt at the parent company and proceeds of an
offering of variable-rate exchangeable debentures at its
pipeline subsidiary.
</TEXT>
