<HL>
   America West August Traffic
</HL>
<DATE>
09/13/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B7
</SO>
<CO>
   AWAL
</CO>
<IN>
AIRLINES (AIR)
</IN>
<LP>
   PHOENIX, Ariz. -- America West Airlines said August
traffic climbed 54% to 1.13 billion revenue passenger miles
from 729 million miles a year earlier. A revenue passenger
mile is one paying passenger carried one mile.
   Load factor, or the percentage of available seats filled,
rose to 67.9% from 61.9%. For the first eight months, America
West said it flew 7.4 billion revenue passenger miles, a 44%
increase from 5.12 billion miles a year earlier. Load factor
was 62.8%, compared with 58%.
</LP>
<TEXT>
</TEXT>
